1
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:38,927
In 1935, Ed Murrow
began his career with CBS.

2
00:02:39,731 --> 00:02:41,391
When World War Two broke out...

3
00:02:41,483 --> 00:02:44,270
...his voice brought
the battle of Britain home to us...

4
00:02:44,361 --> 00:02:46,816
...through his "This Is London"
radio series.

5
00:02:47,739 --> 00:02:49,281
He started with us all...

6
00:02:49,407 --> 00:02:52,823
...many of us here tonight,
when television was in its infancy...

7
00:02:52,911 --> 00:02:55,366
...with the news documentary show,
"See It Now'.

8
00:02:55,538 --> 00:02:57,282
He threw stones at giants.

9
00:02:58,374 --> 00:03:01,624
Segregation, exploitation
of migrant workers...

10
00:03:01,836 --> 00:03:03,912
...apartheid, J. Edgar Hoover...

11
00:03:04,797 --> 00:03:08,925
...not the least of which, his historical
fight with Senator McCarthy.

12
00:03:10,052 --> 00:03:13,671
He is the host of our enormously
popular show "Person to Person"...

13
00:03:14,390 --> 00:03:17,177
...and tonight he is here
with his son, Casey...

14
00:03:17,643 --> 00:03:20,977
...wife, Janet, and all of you
who he's worked with...

15
00:03:21,313 --> 00:03:24,398
...inspired, lectured, and taught.

16
00:03:25,526 --> 00:03:26,854
Ladies and gentlemen...

17
00:03:26,944 --> 00:03:31,107
...the Radio-Television News Directors'
Association and Foundation welcomes...

18
00:03:31,198 --> 00:03:33,440
...Mr. Edward R. Murrow.

19
00:03:54,095 --> 00:03:56,254
This might just do nobody any good.

20
00:03:57,140 --> 00:04:00,888
At the end of this discourse
a few people may accuse this reporter...

21
00:04:00,977 --> 00:04:03,183
...of fouling
his own comfortable nest...

22
00:04:03,605 --> 00:04:07,139
...and your organization may be
accused of having given hospitality...

23
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:09,605
...to heretical
and even dangerous ideas.

24
00:04:10,653 --> 00:04:12,942
But the elaborate structure
of networks...

25
00:04:13,031 --> 00:04:16,862
...advertising agencies, and sponsors
will not be shaken or altered.

26
00:04:17,743 --> 00:04:21,159
It is my desire, if not my duty,
to try to talk to you journeymen...

27
00:04:21,247 --> 00:04:24,782
...with some candor about what
is happening to radio andtelevision.

28
00:04:24,875 --> 00:04:26,833
And if what I say is responsible...

29
00:04:27,253 --> 00:04:29,826
...I alone am responsible
for the saying ofit.

30
00:04:31,048 --> 00:04:33,206
Our history will be
what we make of it.

31
00:04:34,093 --> 00:04:37,675
And if there are any historians
about 50 or 100 years from now...

32
00:04:37,763 --> 00:04:39,387
...and there should be preserved...

33
00:04:39,473 --> 00:04:42,308
...the kinescopes of one week
of all three networks...

34
00:04:42,726 --> 00:04:46,391
...they will there find recorded
in black and white, and in color...

35
00:04:46,980 --> 00:04:49,020
...evidence of decadence,
escapism...

36
00:04:49,107 --> 00:04:52,726
...and insulation from the realities
of the world in which we live.

37
00:04:53,278 --> 00:04:57,062
We are currently wealthy, fat,
comfortable, and complacent.

38
00:04:57,949 --> 00:05:01,614
We have a built-in allergy to
unpleasant or disturbing information.

39
00:05:01,828 --> 00:05:04,034
Our mass media reflect this.

40
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,412
But unless we get up off
our fat surpluses...

41
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,956
...and recognize
that television in the main...

42
00:05:10,044 --> 00:05:14,256
...is being used to distract, delude,
amuse, and insulate us...

43
00:05:14,757 --> 00:05:17,046
...then television
and those who finance it...

44
00:05:17,135 --> 00:05:20,052
...those who look at it
and those who work at it...

45
00:05:20,388 --> 00:05:22,961
...may see atotally
different picture too late.

46
00:06:09,936 --> 00:06:13,139
Millie! Just the person
I wanted to see! Come here!

47
00:06:22,949 --> 00:06:25,107
This goes at the top
of the Roy Campanella piece.

48
00:06:25,201 --> 00:06:26,316
Yes! Give me a half an hour.

49
00:06:26,411 --> 00:06:28,237
I may need it
a little quicker than that!

50
00:06:28,329 --> 00:06:31,449
- Can I get some coffee first?
- Come on! Get me some coffee!

51
00:06:33,543 --> 00:06:34,705
Morning, Johnny!

52
00:06:34,794 --> 00:06:37,914
I have some new notes that go
with the Tito footage for Fred.

53
00:06:38,005 --> 00:06:39,250
Fred's gonna be in
in an hour.

54
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:42,543
I already put them on his desk.
Can you just make sure that...

55
00:06:42,635 --> 00:06:45,422
...he doesn't look at the film
until he reads the notes?

56
00:06:45,513 --> 00:06:46,841
- Yes.
- Thank you.

57
00:06:47,181 --> 00:06:48,212
Hey, Joe! Shirley!

58
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:52,139
- What's going on in here?
- What do you mean?

59
00:06:52,227 --> 00:06:54,137
Two attractive people
alone in the copy room!

60
00:06:54,229 --> 00:06:55,510
Don't tell Paley, he'll fire me.

61
00:06:55,606 --> 00:06:57,100
He'll fire both of us, Shirley.

62
00:06:57,191 --> 00:06:59,978
- Rules are made to be broken!
- You can afford to say that.

63
00:07:04,615 --> 00:07:05,860
Let me see this.

64
00:07:09,494 --> 00:07:13,112
- It's simply a loyalty oath.
- To CBS? - And to America.

65
00:07:13,373 --> 00:07:14,867
You promise to be a loyal American?

66
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:17,116
I know. All of the reporters
have signed this.

67
00:07:17,210 --> 00:07:18,918
Who are you promising this to?
CBS?

68
00:07:19,004 --> 00:07:20,996
Fred signed it.
Murrow signed it.

69
00:07:21,089 --> 00:07:22,464
- Murrow signed it?
- Yeah.

70
00:07:23,925 --> 00:07:25,668
Are you now
or have you ever been...

71
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:28,002
I thought it was a joke,
but there's a lot of pressure.

72
00:07:28,096 --> 00:07:30,634
...on the Attorney General's list
of subversive groups?

73
00:07:30,723 --> 00:07:32,930
- I don't know.
- Let's think about it.

74
00:07:33,017 --> 00:07:36,600
What is it really saying? Is it a civil
liberties issue or censorship?

75
00:07:36,687 --> 00:07:39,013
Am I simply stating to CBS
that I'm not a Communist?

76
00:07:39,107 --> 00:07:41,432
- Murrow signed this?
- And Fred and Stanton.

77
00:07:41,526 --> 00:07:44,692
- Maybe you should talk toMurrow.
- Maybe I should sign it.

78
00:07:45,863 --> 00:07:48,650
If you don't sign this,
are you and I a target?

79
00:07:50,951 --> 00:07:52,909
If I don'tsign it,
they'll fire me.

80
00:07:59,376 --> 00:08:00,372
Sign it.

81
00:08:00,794 --> 00:08:02,953
Finally we can tell everyone
the truth.

82
00:08:04,256 --> 00:08:07,672
If I could express it
in what's in my heart now...

83
00:08:08,051 --> 00:08:12,429
...I'd do it in the terms
of the poet who once said...

84
00:08:13,015 --> 00:08:16,383
..."Ah, 'tis but a dainty flower
I bring to you."

85
00:08:17,394 --> 00:08:19,433
'Yes, 'tis but a violet..."

86
00:08:20,397 --> 00:08:21,891
"...glistening with dew."

87
00:08:22,899 --> 00:08:26,434
"But still in its heart
there lie beauties concealed."

88
00:08:27,529 --> 00:08:29,189
"So in our heart..."

89
00:08:30,615 --> 00:08:32,193
"...our love for you..."

90
00:08:33,201 --> 00:08:35,774
"...lies unrevealed."

91
00:08:38,289 --> 00:08:39,404
I used to...

92
00:08:45,588 --> 00:08:50,582
...pride myself on the idea
that I was a bit... tough...

93
00:08:52,386 --> 00:08:58,590
...especially over the past
19-19 months, when we've been...

94
00:08:59,226 --> 00:09:02,263
...kicked around,
and bullwhipped, and damned.

95
00:09:03,564 --> 00:09:04,892
I didnt think that...

96
00:09:07,192 --> 00:09:10,193
...I could be... touched very deeply.

97
00:09:10,404 --> 00:09:12,646
Okay, that's enough.
That's enough, Leo.

98
00:09:12,739 --> 00:09:14,779
- It's short.
- Howlong is the piece?

99
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:16,610
It's 4 minutes,
but we can cut it down.

100
00:09:16,702 --> 00:09:19,489
It cant stand alone, but it might be
a nice companion piece.

101
00:09:19,580 --> 00:09:21,905
Let's go through this one more time.
Palmer!

102
00:09:21,999 --> 00:09:25,332
Yep, got a call from the office
of Senator Morse this morning...

103
00:09:25,419 --> 00:09:28,538
...interested in setting up
a debate possibly with Senator Kerr...

104
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:31,086
...over the comments
Bentsen made on last night's show.

105
00:09:31,174 --> 00:09:34,424
Secretary of Agriculture? Good idea!
Can they do it by this week?

106
00:09:34,511 --> 00:09:37,084
No, it would have to be 2 weeks
at the earliest...

107
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:40,513
...depending on Morse's schedule.
But still it's a great idea.

108
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,933
Let's follow up on that.
"Hoover speaks on Benjamin Franklin."

109
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:47,140
We're having better luck
with Mr. Benjamin Frankin...

110
00:09:47,231 --> 00:09:48,476
...than with Mr. Hoover.

111
00:09:48,566 --> 00:09:51,022
It may progress better
as a "Person to Person".

112
00:09:51,110 --> 00:09:53,566
"At home with Ben Frankin.
His electricity awards."

113
00:09:53,654 --> 00:09:55,564
We've got the footage,
we need to contact him.

114
00:09:55,656 --> 00:09:59,357
See if you can contact him and get the
shot. He wants to do the story. Joe!

115
00:09:59,452 --> 00:10:01,195
Member Delbert Clark?
No longer with us.

116
00:10:01,287 --> 00:10:03,825
- New York Times? - Yeah.
- Our friend at the Times.

117
00:10:03,914 --> 00:10:06,619
This was yesterday morning,
they're saying it's...

118
00:10:06,834 --> 00:10:10,417
- How old was he?
- 53. Sudden illness.

119
00:10:10,504 --> 00:10:13,173
- Home of a friend.
- No, it's not a nobit piece.

120
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:15,878
Natalie send some flowers
over there from us.

121
00:10:16,343 --> 00:10:18,668
Couple things.
Case before the Supreme Court...

122
00:10:18,762 --> 00:10:22,676
...involving the constitutionality of a
section of the Internal Security Act...

123
00:10:22,766 --> 00:10:24,723
...provides for the deportation
of any alien...

124
00:10:24,810 --> 00:10:27,561
...if he becomes a Communist
after entering this country.

125
00:10:28,105 --> 00:10:29,184
Can you take this?

126
00:10:29,272 --> 00:10:31,846
All right. McCarthy interrupting
his wedding trip...

127
00:10:31,942 --> 00:10:35,441
...to take charge of the investigation
of Communist infiltration...

128
00:10:35,529 --> 00:10:37,936
- Natalie, send some flowers.
- Poor Mrs. McCarthy!

129
00:10:38,031 --> 00:10:40,154
May I finish?
It's national security!

130
00:10:40,241 --> 00:10:43,029
- A real ladies' man!
- Well, they're in love.

131
00:10:43,536 --> 00:10:47,914
We have no show for Tuesday, fellows.
So get out there and make some news.

132
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:52,083
Rob a bank. Mug an old lady.
Do something.

133
00:10:52,879 --> 00:10:55,500
- You look at the Secretary Stevens
footage? - We will.

134
00:10:55,590 --> 00:10:58,128
Watch it all the way to the end,
it's worth it.

135
00:10:59,719 --> 00:11:00,917
Thank you, John.

136
00:11:01,846 --> 00:11:03,221
There's notmuch there.

137
00:11:03,347 --> 00:11:06,847
I can't tie it to the Eisenhower
in the back of the train piece.

138
00:11:07,143 --> 00:11:10,512
- You ever spend any time in Detroit,
Fred? - Not recently.

139
00:11:11,897 --> 00:11:15,147
There's a story here
in the Detroit News, Dexter, Michigan.

140
00:11:15,901 --> 00:11:17,977
A kid named Milo Radulovich.

141
00:11:19,572 --> 00:11:23,320
- Italian? - Irish. Air Force
kicked him out because his dad...

142
00:11:23,409 --> 00:11:28,035
...reads ome Serbian newspaper.
- Was he a Communist? - I don't know.

143
00:11:28,122 --> 00:11:29,948
- Who brought the charges?
- Air Force.

144
00:11:30,749 --> 00:11:33,370
Charges were in a sealed envelope,
nobody saw them.

145
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:36,746
- Not even at the hearing? - He was
declared guilty without a trial...

146
00:11:36,838 --> 00:11:38,582
...and told if he wanted
to keep his job...

147
00:11:38,673 --> 00:11:41,959
...he had to denounce his father
and his sister. Thank you, Natalie.

148
00:11:42,052 --> 00:11:44,507
- His sister?
- He told them to take a hike.

149
00:11:46,223 --> 00:11:49,888
Let's send Joe and Charlie down there,
see if he's any good on camera.

150
00:11:49,976 --> 00:11:52,265
Is he being brought
before the Committee?

151
00:11:52,979 --> 00:11:53,975
No.

152
00:11:55,106 --> 00:11:56,481
Then it's not McCarthy.

153
00:11:58,109 --> 00:11:59,105
Isn't it?

154
00:12:05,199 --> 00:12:06,741
Milo Radulovich.

155
00:12:10,997 --> 00:12:12,407
What happens to your children...

156
00:12:12,498 --> 00:12:15,416
...your 5-year-old and your 5-month-old
in terms of you?

157
00:12:15,501 --> 00:12:18,455
If I am being judged
on my relatives...

158
00:12:19,463 --> 00:12:24,540
...are my children going
to be asked to denounce me?

159
00:12:24,635 --> 00:12:28,680
Are they going to be judged
on what their father was labeled?

160
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:34,384
Are they going to have to explain
to their friends, etc...

161
00:12:34,478 --> 00:12:36,803
...why their father
is a security risk?

162
00:12:37,773 --> 00:12:42,435
If the thing is let stand
as it, the first recommendation...

163
00:12:42,736 --> 00:12:46,947
...was sent out by the board,
I see a chain reaction that...

164
00:12:47,741 --> 00:12:50,030
...has no end to anybody,
for anybody.

165
00:12:56,708 --> 00:12:58,036
Well, that's new.

166
00:12:59,252 --> 00:13:00,877
You can't call this
a neutral piece.

167
00:13:00,962 --> 00:13:04,248
The other side's been represented
rather well for the last 2 years.

168
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:05,918
The Air Force
hasn't gone on the record.

169
00:13:06,009 --> 00:13:09,045
So you want to forego the standards
you've stuck to for 15 years...

170
00:13:09,137 --> 00:13:10,382
...both sides, no commentary.

171
00:13:10,471 --> 00:13:13,472
- We all editorialize. - I'm just
making sure we identify what...

172
00:13:13,558 --> 00:13:15,218
We're giving them
the information up front...

173
00:13:15,309 --> 00:13:16,887
...and we're asking them
to comment on it.

174
00:13:16,978 --> 00:13:18,009
Frank, hold on.

175
00:13:18,771 --> 00:13:20,431
I've searched my conscience.

176
00:13:20,606 --> 00:13:23,809
I can't for the life of me
find any justification for this.

177
00:13:23,901 --> 00:13:26,772
I simply cannot accept
that there are, on every story...

178
00:13:26,862 --> 00:13:28,902
...two equal and logical sides
to an argument.

179
00:13:28,989 --> 00:13:31,943
- Call it editorializing, if you'd like.
- It is editorializing.

180
00:13:32,034 --> 00:13:33,742
They'll have equal time
to defend themselves.

181
00:13:33,827 --> 00:13:35,903
Do you understand the position
you're putting us in?

182
00:13:35,996 --> 00:13:38,950
We are all in this together,
if the Senate wants to investigate...

183
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:40,072
Do me a favor...

184
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:43,500
...avoid any big speeches about how
we're all in a big boat together!

185
00:13:43,587 --> 00:13:44,785
Please, don't insult me.

186
00:13:45,339 --> 00:13:49,467
I have to go back to Mr. Paley
and Alcoa, who sponsors your show...

187
00:13:49,968 --> 00:13:52,293
...and also have
some military contracts...

188
00:13:52,387 --> 00:13:55,590
...and I have to tell them that
they're going to be in a tough bind...

189
00:13:55,682 --> 00:13:57,722
...because of a beef you had
with Joe McCarthy.

190
00:13:57,809 --> 00:14:00,929
- We're not going at McCarthy.
- You're starting the goddamn fire.

191
00:14:01,021 --> 00:14:04,390
Excuse me. Mr. Friendly,
there's a Colonel Anderson to see you?

192
00:14:04,482 --> 00:14:07,982
- Colonel? - He's in your office.
There are two of them.

193
00:14:09,779 --> 00:14:13,029
Maybe they liked the transcript,
and want to compliment us on it.

194
00:14:13,616 --> 00:14:14,647
Excuse me.

195
00:14:22,834 --> 00:14:25,585
Go after Joe Kennedy.
We'll pay for it.

196
00:14:26,087 --> 00:14:28,163
I've got a great story about Hoover.

197
00:14:32,134 --> 00:14:34,590
You know how many shows
you're going to have to do...

198
00:14:34,678 --> 00:14:37,763
...to make up for this? - And Judy
and her daughter Liza next week.

199
00:14:37,848 --> 00:14:39,924
No, no.
You're interviewing Rin Tin Tin!

200
00:14:45,022 --> 00:14:46,564
I'll talk to Mr. Paley.

201
00:14:49,151 --> 00:14:50,978
Alcoa wont pay for the ads.

202
00:14:51,987 --> 00:14:55,652
And we probably wont either.
But nobody'll stop you.

203
00:14:55,741 --> 00:14:56,903
How much are the ads?

204
00:14:59,161 --> 00:15:02,327
- 3,000.
- I'll split it with Fred.

205
00:15:03,915 --> 00:15:07,249
He just won't have Christmas presents
for his kids this year.

206
00:15:07,586 --> 00:15:10,789
- He's a Jew. - Don't tell him that,
he loves Christmas.

207
00:15:19,973 --> 00:15:22,973
- To be clear, you did speak
with the lawyers? - Yes, we did.

208
00:15:23,059 --> 00:15:26,344
And we read the transcript. We've not
been allowed to see the footage.

209
00:15:26,437 --> 00:15:29,474
Mack is on a plane from Dexter
right now with the last interviews.

210
00:15:29,565 --> 00:15:31,309
We'll be going
right down to the wire.

211
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:36,062
Your show airs tomorrow. How can we
possibly approve and check...

212
00:15:36,155 --> 00:15:39,856
...your story in the limited amount
of time you have given us?

213
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:43,651
With all due respect, you have been
invited to participate in this piece...

214
00:15:43,746 --> 00:15:45,121
...not to approve it.

215
00:15:45,748 --> 00:15:48,784
We are going with the story
that says that the U.S. Air Force...

216
00:15:48,876 --> 00:15:51,414
...tried Milo Radulovich
without any evidence...

217
00:15:51,503 --> 00:15:54,077
...and found him guilty
of being a security risk...

218
00:15:54,173 --> 00:15:57,838
...without his Constitutional rights...
- You have not seen the evidence...

219
00:15:57,926 --> 00:16:00,251
...and are claiming
he's not a security risk.

220
00:16:00,345 --> 00:16:04,473
Wouldn't you guess that those who have
seen the contents of that envelope...

221
00:16:04,558 --> 00:16:08,602
...might have a better idea of what
makes someone a danger to his country?

222
00:16:08,687 --> 00:16:12,020
- Who? Who? - Or do you think
it should just be you that decides?

223
00:16:12,107 --> 00:16:14,680
Who are the people?
Are they elected? Are they appointed?

224
00:16:14,776 --> 00:16:17,445
Do they have an axe to grind?
Is it you, sir?

225
00:16:17,696 --> 00:16:21,942
Or you, Colonel Jenkns? Do you know
the contents of that sealed envelope?

226
00:16:22,951 --> 00:16:28,490
We have been a friend and ally of both
Mr. Murrow and CBS News for many years.

227
00:16:29,082 --> 00:16:32,367
The story you are going
to run tomorrow is without merit.

228
00:16:32,877 --> 00:16:35,997
So before you take any steps
that cannot be undone...

229
00:16:36,380 --> 00:16:39,050
...I strongly urge you
to reconsider your stand.

230
