355
00:26:05,352 --> 00:26:07,510
- Good evening, Lee.
- Good evening, Ed.

356
00:26:07,604 --> 00:26:12,349
- What are you doing? - I'm dictating
my weekly syndicated newspaper column...

357
00:26:12,818 --> 00:26:19,354
...and on my trusty tape recorder here,
I'm also dictating a book.

358
00:26:19,449 --> 00:26:21,821
- It's an inspirational book.
- Lee, what about you?

359
00:26:21,910 --> 00:26:24,911
Have you given much thought
to getting married and settling down?

360
00:26:24,996 --> 00:26:27,617
Actually, I've given
a lot of thought to it...

361
00:26:27,707 --> 00:26:31,621
...but I don't believe in getting married
just for the sake of getting married.

362
00:26:31,711 --> 00:26:34,416
I want to someday
find the perfect mate...

363
00:26:34,797 --> 00:26:38,877
...and settle down to what I hope will
be a marriage that will be blessed...

364
00:26:39,010 --> 00:26:41,631
...by faith
and will be a lasting union.

365
00:26:42,138 --> 00:26:46,883
I was reading
about lovely young Princess Margaret...

366
00:26:47,435 --> 00:26:50,104
...and she's lookng
for her dream man, too...

367
00:26:50,688 --> 00:26:52,680
...and I hope she finds him someday.

368
00:26:54,066 --> 00:26:57,815
Uh-huh. Lee, thanks very much
for letting us come and visit you.

369
00:26:57,903 --> 00:26:59,066
It's been very pleasant.

370
00:26:59,155 --> 00:27:01,313
And will you say goodnight
to your family for us?

371
00:27:01,407 --> 00:27:03,115
- I certainly will.
- Thanks a lot.

372
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:05,027
- Good night, Ed.
- Good night, Lee.

373
00:27:06,495 --> 00:27:09,247
Next week, we'll take you
