- Ed!

385
00:28:07,388 --> 00:28:08,798
You're getting good at this!

386
00:28:09,348 --> 00:28:11,139
They're gonna think you like it!

387
00:28:11,308 --> 00:28:13,597
Pays the bills. How are you, Don?

388
00:28:14,895 --> 00:28:15,926
Ah, it's...

389
00:28:17,397 --> 00:28:18,596
...day today.

390
00:28:19,358 --> 00:28:22,275
If she saw how good you look
right now, she'd be back.

391
00:28:23,820 --> 00:28:26,228
You tell her that
if you see her, will you?

392
00:28:27,741 --> 00:28:30,944
- I read the O'Brian piece.
- Yeah, it's tough.

393
00:28:31,787 --> 00:28:34,360
I'm a pinko.
I slant the news.

394
00:28:35,457 --> 00:28:38,292
I'm just waiting for him
to say my wife left me too.

395
00:28:38,585 --> 00:28:41,502
- Nobody worth their salt reads him.
- You read him.

396
00:28:42,047 --> 00:28:43,706
Well, see, I rest my case.

397
00:28:45,425 --> 00:28:49,672
- Does Paley read him?
- Bill Paley's not gonna do anything.

398
00:28:52,849 --> 00:28:53,963
Thanks, Ed.

399
00:28:55,309 --> 00:28:58,595
I just came by to tell you
how great the Lieutenant piece was.

400
00:28:58,688 --> 00:29:01,891
- Thanks. - How's the fallout?
- Mostly good, surprisingly.

401
00:29:02,108 --> 00:29:04,895
Is this the start?
Are you taking sides?

402
00:29:07,488 --> 00:29:10,524
It's just a little poke
with a stick, see what happens.

403
00:29:10,783 --> 00:29:12,491
You let me know if I can help.

404
00:29:12,701 --> 00:29:14,160
But you're a pinko.

405
00:29:16,914 --> 00:29:18,159
I'll see you.

406
00:29:34,139 --> 00:29:36,808
Hey, Joe! What's all this
Radulovich junk you're putting out?

407
00:29:36,892 --> 00:29:39,809
I can't talk to you now. I have
to get this film back to New York.

408
00:29:39,895 --> 00:29:41,223
What would you say if I told you...

409
00:29:41,313 --> 00:29:43,886
