414
00:30:04,502 --> 00:30:06,625
You're supposed to slip it
into my briefcase!

415
00:30:06,712 --> 00:30:09,879
I didnt know who to give
this information to, Paley or Murrow.

416
00:30:09,966 --> 00:30:13,548
As you can imagine, Fred and I
aren't very friendly. No pun intended.

417
00:30:13,928 --> 00:30:15,422
No pun elocuted.

418
00:30:18,891 --> 00:30:20,884
- What do you got, Donald?
- In short?

419
00:30:21,143 --> 00:30:23,895
Murrows been a Communist
sympathizer since the 1930's.

420
00:30:23,979 --> 00:30:27,514
Member of the International Workers,
sponsored educational trips to Moscow...

421
00:30:27,608 --> 00:30:30,146
...and on the Sovietpayroll
in 1935. It's all there.

422
00:30:30,235 --> 00:30:32,109
You wanna know
why that's not possible?

423
00:30:32,196 --> 00:30:33,690
Why you'll lose this one?

424
00:30:34,156 --> 00:30:36,148
Because everyone in this country...

425
00:30:36,241 --> 00:30:39,361
...knows that Ed Murrow
is a loyal American, he's apatriot.

426
00:30:41,330 --> 00:30:44,081
Did you know the word "gullible"
isn't in the dictionary?

427
00:30:44,166 --> 00:30:47,166
- Can I give this to him?
- I'd love it! I have copies!

428
00:30:50,255 --> 00:30:51,797
I think you guys go too far.

429
00:30:52,173 --> 00:30:54,499
Well, if it walks like a duck,
talks like a duck.

430
00:31:01,349 --> 00:31:02,677
Yes, Mr. Paley.

431
00:31:03,685 --> 00:31:05,309
Right away.
Yes, sir.

432
00:31:07,021 --> 00:31:08,480
No, he hasn't called.

433
00:31:09,774 --> 00:31:13,606
Yes, sir, the second he calls.
If you're in a meeting, shall I?

434
00:31:14,946 --> 00:31:16,819
Yes, sir.
Of course, sir.

435
00:31:19,575 --> 00:31:20,654
Mr. Murrow!

436
00:31:21,535 --> 00:31:23,279
